NYT of June 13, 1915
  <a href="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F10E12FF3D5512738FDDAA0994DE405B858DF1D3" rel="nofollow">select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F10E12FF3D551273...</a>
reports that &quot;Hundreds of children shouted &quot;Hurrah!&quot; and waved their hats and their hands yesterday afternoon as little Fred Lewis, 5 years old, of 275 West 150th Street, and William J. Lee, Supervisor of Recreations of the Department of Parks, sent the Stars and Stripes fluttering to the pinnacle of a tall flagpole, and Astor Field, a children's playground, was dedicated. &quot;
